The paper focuses on the performance of shuffling operations in MapReduce in the context of data center networks (DCNs), which suggests that it falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) models to analyze the impact of link failures on performance suggests that it could also fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses completion time degradations, which suggests that it could fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of DCN topologies and the analysis of different performance metrics suggest that it could also fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
